 {"id": "franken_networkx-btneg", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] balanced_tree/binomial_tree with negative args raised OverflowError instead of nx empty-graph behavior", "description": "nx.balanced_tree(-1, 3) returns an empty Graph; nx.binomial_tree(-1) returns a 1-node graph. fnx passed negative args straight to the Rust binding which crashed with OverflowError on usize conversion. Short-circuit negative inputs to match nx exactly.", "status": "closed", "priority": 4, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:35:24.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:35:24.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:35:24.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Short-circuit negative inputs", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-gnpvalid", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] gnp_random_graph/fast_gnp_random_graph with negative n raised OverflowError instead of NetworkXError", "description": "nx raises NetworkXError(\"Negative number of nodes not valid: -1\"); fnx crashed with Rust OverflowError via usize conversion. Added pre-validation guard.", "status": "closed", "priority": 4, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:35:24.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:35:24.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:35:24.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Added negative-n guard", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-astarnop", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] astar_path raised ValueError instead of NetworkXNoPath with wrong message", "description": "fnx.astar_path / astar_path_length raised ValueError with \"No path between X and Y.\" on disconnected inputs. nx raises NetworkXNoPath with \"Node Y not reachable from X\". User code with except nx.NetworkXNoPath silently missed fnx errors. Translated the Rust ValueError to the nx-shaped NetworkXNoPath at the wrapper edge.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:44:07.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:44:07.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:44:07.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Translate Rust ValueError to NetworkXNoPath", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-nbunchseq", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] cut_size/edge_boundary/etc TypeErrored when nbunch was a set", "description": "fnx cut_size/normalized_cut_size/edge_boundary/node_boundary threw TypeError when S/T/nbunch1/nbunch2 was a set, dict_keys, generator, or other non-Sequence iterable. nx accepts any iterable. Added _coerce_nbunch helper that lists-materialises non-tuple/list input. edge_expansion(G, S={0,1,2,3}) and similar composition chains now work.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:46:21.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:46:21.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:46:21.000000000Z", "close_reason": "_coerce_nbunch helper", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-mutiter", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] mutation during nodes() iteration silently allowed while nx raises RuntimeError", "description": "fnx.Graph.nodes() returns a list (snapshot); nx returns a dict view that detects concurrent modification. User code mutating during iteration gets silent behavior on fnx but clear RuntimeError on nx. Queued \u2014 a full fix requires changing the iteration contract which is a deeper architectural change.", "status": "open", "priority": 4, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:46:21.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:46:21.000000000Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
